e Ranger) to fending off bizarre accusations of sexual and emotional abuse =
by multiple women (he=E2=80=99s said they were consensual affairs), is now =
=E2=80=9Cturning down=E2=80=9D roles. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s slow, but gener=
ally now the conversation when my name comes up with people in the industry=
 is, =E2=80=98Man, that guy got fucked.=E2=80=99 And that feels really good=
,=E2=80=9D he said on a recent podcast.=C2=A0

To that end, Hammer has booked a couple
indies, and he now has attorney Todd Rubenstein at the prominent Yorn Levin=
e firm representing him. I=E2=80=99ve heard that at least two management fi=
rms are interested, too. If the offers are indeed coming in, I could even s=
ee UTA, home to Hammer=E2=80=99s former agent Brandon Liebman, taking him o=
n.
* Kevin Tsujihara=E2=80=94I spotted the former Warner Bros. C.E.O. a couple=
 months ago in a prime booth at
the Polo Lounge. It=E2=80=99s been nearly six years since he stepped down a=
fter a Hollywood Reporter investigation revealed that he sought auditions f=
or an actress with whom he=E2=80=99d had a sexual relationship. Since then,=
 he=E2=80=99s been investing in media businesses via Alignment Capital, whi=
ch he started with Jeff Bewkes and Alex Iosilevich. Could a studio or strea=
mer executive job be next?
* Scott
Rudin=E2=80=94The former uber-producer has been sidelined since his bullyin=
g behavior was publicly exposed in 2021. He=E2=80=99s stayed involved behin=
d the scenes, and has been making calls lately to industry friends. The que=
stion is when Rudin will publicly step out as back.
* Roy Price=E2=80=94The former Amazon Studios head, who left after a produc=
er accused him of abusive behavior, has been writing a book and a Substack
newsletter=E2=80=94and criticizing ( https://x.com/RoyPrice/status/18761285=
29521504727?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F9%2F25%2=
